=> start

~ start
[wait=1]...Dad, where are you?
...
Sarah: [wait=1]...Oh. Hello. 
Sarah: You seen my father?
Sarah: I heard him come in late last night. I'm a light sleeper. I could even hear you snore.
Sarah: But then he left again... and didn't come back.
- Haven't seen him since yesterday, myself. 
	Sarah: Hmm. Wonder what he's up to. => drink
- Know where he went?
	Sarah: Uh, not really. => drink

~ drink
Sarah: He used to drink. A lot. But he hasn't in a while.
Sarah: Don't remember him being gone for a whole night since he stopped. 
Sarah: I'm starting to get worried. 
- I'm sure he's fine. => what
- I can help you look for him, if you want. => help
- The Goddess is looking out for him. Don't worry. [if Variables.get_var("religious_fervour") >=6] 
	Sarah: I'm sure She is. But it's a bit more complicated than that. => hope
- Isn't the Goddess supposed to take care of him? Him being a Gift-bearer and whatnot? [if Variables.get_var("religious_fervour") <= 5]
	Sarah: That's not how it works. Gift-bearers don't get special treatment. => hope

~ what
Sarah: How can you be sure? You just got here. 
Sarah: You don't know the first thing about us. 
- I was just trying to comfort you. 
	Sarah: I don't want comfort. I want to find him. => hope
- You're right. I've no idea if he's fine or not. 
	Sarah: Oh, this is bad. => hope
- I don't know. It's just a thing you say. 
	Sarah: I hate it when adults just say things. => hope
- I'm the Goddess's chosen one. If I say he's fine, then he's fine. [if Variables.get_var("religious_fervour") >=6]
	Sarah: Uh huh. That's definitely not how it works. => hope

