~ beat
Sarah: What? No! Of course not!
Sarah: Why would you think that?
Sarah: He's the sweetest, most caring dad in the world. He loves me more than anything. 
Sarah: He'd never lay a hand on me. 
- Just asking. 
	Sarah: Weird thing to ask. 
	- Not really. 
		Sarah: Yes really. You won't find that kind of thing here. The Goddess is strictly against it. => children
	- Guess so. 
		Sarah: You won't find that kind of thing here, you know. The Goddess is strictly against it. => children
- Lots of heavy drinkers are also violent. That's all. 
	Sarah: Yeah, well, you won't find that kind of thing here. => children
- Got some bad experiences with it myself. Just wanted to make sure. 
	Sarah: Oh, I'm sorry to hear that. 
	Sarah: But no. Like I said, he would never. 
	Sarah: And anyway, you won't find that kind of thing here. The Goddess is strictly against it. => children

~ children
Sarah: She says children are pure and holy. We're the future, the ones who will inhabit Her new world, once She's done cleansing it of sinners and evil-doers. 
Sarah: Parents who beat their children are punished. Maybe even killed.
Sarah: But that's never happened here, cause no ever does it. 
- Good to know. => anyway
- Built yourselves a proper little utopia here, have you?
	Sarah: Not sure what you mean by utopia. But we didn't build anything. It's all the work of the Goddess. 
	Sarah: She loves us and She takes care of us. We're all indebted to Her for life. => anyway
	
~ anyway
Sarah: Anyway, he's been clean three months now. Not a single sip. 
Sarah: I've been watching him. 
- You keep doing that. 
	Sarah: Course I will. He needs me even more than I need him. 
	Sarah: It was the Goddess who told him to stop. If he drinks again, he's in trouble. => vengeful
- He's lucky to have you. 
	Sarah: Course he is. And there's more than this one reason for it. He needs me even more than I need him. 
	Sarah: It was the Goddess who told him to stop, you know? So if he drinks again, he's in trouble. => vengeful
- Lay off him a bit, eh? 
	Sarah: Can't do that. It was the Goddess who told him to stop. If he drinks again, he's in trouble. => vengeful
	
~ vengeful 
- The Goddess is vengeful, isn't She?
	Sarah: She can be. She can also be merciful and fair. 
	Sarah: She's whatever She needs to be. 
	Sarah: It's not for us to question Her. 
	- If you say so. 
		Sarah: It's not so because I say so. It is so because She says so. => micah
	- You speak the truth. [if Variables.get_var("religious_fervour") >= 6]
		Sarah: Course I am. [do Variables.mod_var("religious_fervour", 1)] => micah
	- Guess you're right. 
		Sarah: Course I am. => micah
	- Eh, not sure how I feel about that. 
		Sarah: You'll see the light, eventually. 
	- That's... not how it should work. [if Variables.get_var("religious_fervour") <= 5]
		Sarah: Who are you to say? You should know your place. => micah
- What kind of trouble?
	Sarah: I don't know. It's not for me to say. 
	Sarah: But it sure won't be pretty. She very rarely gives orders directly to us, mortals, individually. 
	Sarah: She must have had Her reasons, and they must have been important. 
	Sarah: So I gotta be super careful and make sure my dad doesn't disobey Her. 
	Sarah: I love him and I'm sure he loves the Goddess, but he has his moments of weakness from time to time. 
	- I see. => micah
	- Weakness? 
		Sarah: I've seen him nearly cry over the most unimportant things sometimes. Things outside his control. I don't get it. 
		Sarah: Anyway, that's our business. => micah

~ micah
Micah: [wait=1.5]Morning, Sarah. Fresh delivery for you, novice. Hahah. You already look like you own the place.
#add items
Sarah: Micah! Have you seen my father? He didn't come home last night.
Micah: Sure have. He's with the Elders. No idea why, though. He was with 'em late into the night. 
Micah: I tried to listen in but couldn't hear shit. 
Micah: ...Uh, sorry.
Micah: He just up and left at one point. He seemed angry.
Micah: He came back this morning. He's still there, now. I think.
Sarah: Oh thank the Goddess. I was starting to get worried. 
Sarah: Thought he started drinking again. I'll have a word with him tonight. 
Sarah: Anyway, I'm ready. Shall we?
Micah: Uh, sure. 
- Where are you two going?
	Micah: Uh, we can't tell you. [do Variables.set_var("knows_of_gift", "true")]
